# Trivy waivers — pgvector image only (wired to the pgvector scan step in
# .github/workflows/ci.yml via the `trivyignores:` input; NOT applied to the
# neo4j or ollama scans, which stay strict).
#
# Context (Issue #4): the relational store is pinned to
# pgvector/pgvector:0.8.2-pg17-trixie. 0.8.2 is the CVE-fix release that
# supersedes the original 0.8.1 pin; trixie (Debian 13.4) is the cleanest base
# pgvector ships — 9 OS CVEs vs bookworm's 13, and pgvector has no UBI variant.
#
# Two unusual things about this waiver, both deliberate and pre-approved:
#
#   1. AGE BEND (spec §6.7, "no exceptions without explicit conversation").
#      Every pgvector tag — all PG majors, both bases — was rebuilt 2026-05-15.
#      0.8.2-pg17-trixie was therefore 6 days old at pin time (2026-05-21),
#      inside the 7-day image soak. Pinned anyway, by explicit user decision:
#      it is a CVE-*fix* release from a known official publisher, a serious
#      flaw in a ~6-day-old rebuild would most likely already be public, and
#      waiting only prolongs exposure to the *known* CVEs the bump addresses.
#
#   2. OS-PACKAGE CVEs ARE WAIVED HERE (atypical — normally we *fix* OS CVEs by
#      choosing a fresher rebuild or a cleaner base, never waive them). There
#      is no fresher rebuild to move to: 0.8.2-pg17-trixie IS the newest pgvector
#      image, and these are freshly-disclosed Debian advisories whose fixes
#      (deb13u1/deb13u4/257.13 etc.) upstream has not yet baked into a rebuild.
#      Going *older* is strictly worse (0.8.1-pg17-trixie carries 42 OS CVEs).
#      So the only choices were "wait for an upstream rebuild" or "pin now and
#      waive with justification"; the latter was chosen after a per-CVE RCE
#      assessment (below) confirmed none is a network-reachable RCE in this
#      127.0.0.1-bound, single-user, non-root, no-new-privileges deployment.
#
# All waivers across images are also indexed in infra/trivy/WAIVERS.md (the
# review register: fixed-in versions + drop conditions, checked periodically).
#
# Revisit: every pgvector tag bump. Drop the OS entries the moment a rebuilt
# pgvector image ships Debian's fixed packages (re-scan should pass without
# them); drop the gosu/stdlib entries when upstream rebuilds gosu on a patched
# Go toolchain.

# ───────────────────────── OS packages (Debian 13.4) ─────────────────────────
# None reachable as RCE here. Postgres's own TLS uses OpenSSL, not gnutls;
# gnutls is only a transitive library. DTLS is never used. No systemd/D-Bus
# daemon runs in the container (Postgres is PID 1 via gosu). Bound to 127.0.0.1,
# single trusted user. See per-CVE notes.

# CVE-2026-42010 — gnutls (CRITICAL): TLS authentication bypass via NUL byte in
# username. Not reachable: Postgres TLS is OpenSSL-based; gnutls handles no auth
# path we expose.
CVE-2026-42010
# CVE-2026-33845 — gnutls (CRITICAL): DoS via DTLS zero-length fragment. DoS
# only, and no DTLS endpoint exists.
CVE-2026-33845
# CVE-2026-33846 — gnutls (HIGH): DoS via heap buffer overflow in DTLS
# handshake. DoS, no DTLS path.
CVE-2026-33846
# CVE-2026-3833 — gnutls (HIGH): policy bypass, case-sensitive nameConstraints
# comparison. Cert-validation correctness bug, not RCE; gnutls unused for our TLS.
CVE-2026-3833
# CVE-2026-42009 — gnutls (HIGH): DoS via DTLS packet reordering. DoS, no DTLS.
CVE-2026-42009
# CVE-2026-42011 — gnutls (HIGH): security bypass via incorrect name-constraint
# handling. Not RCE; gnutls unused for our TLS.
CVE-2026-42011
# CVE-2026-29111 — systemd/libsystemd0+libudev1 (HIGH): unprivileged IPC API call with
# malformed data causes systemd to assert and freeze (v250+) or corrupt the stack
# (v249-) — DoS, not arbitrary code execution (earlier description over-claimed exec).
# This image runs no systemd init and no D-Bus, so the IPC attack surface is absent —
# libsystemd0/libudev1 are linked libraries only.
CVE-2026-29111
# CVE-2026-4878 — libcap2 (HIGH): local privilege escalation via TOCTOU race in
# cap_set_file(). Requires an already-present local unprivileged attacker inside
# the container; no remote vector.
CVE-2026-4878
# CVE-2026-40356 — krb5 (HIGH): MIT Kerberos 5 integer *underflow* in NegoEx
# mechanism causes OOB read → DoS (process crash on gss_accept_sec_context). Applies
# to libgssapi-krb5-2 / libk5crypto3 / libkrb5-3 / libkrb5support0 (linked libs
# only — this image runs no Kerberos service and Postgres uses OpenSSL for TLS).
# Fixed in Debian 1.21.3-5+deb13u1; not yet baked into a pgvector rebuild.
# Disclosed in the wave after the Issue #4 waivers landed (2026-05-26). Earlier
# description said "integer overflow" — actually underflow (corrected 2026-05-27
# during the post-PR-23 audit).
CVE-2026-40356

# ──────────────── Bundled dependency: gosu Go stdlib (gobinary) ───────────────
# gosu is a setuid step-down wrapper: it drops root and exec()s Postgres. It
# opens no sockets, makes no TLS connection, and parses no URLs, archives, or
# mail — so every one of these stdlib CVEs sits in unreachable code. Identical
# across all base variants; fixable only by an upstream gosu rebuild on a patched
# Go toolchain. Same class as the neo4j netty waiver.

# CVE-2025-68121 — crypto/tls (CRITICAL): incorrect cert validation on TLS
# session resumption. gosu makes no TLS connections.
CVE-2025-68121
# CVE-2025-58183 — archive/tar (HIGH): unbounded allocation parsing GNU sparse map.
CVE-2025-58183
# CVE-2025-61726 — net/url (HIGH): memory exhaustion in query-parameter parsing.
CVE-2025-61726
# CVE-2025-61728 — archive/zip (HIGH): excessive CPU building archive index.
CVE-2025-61728
# CVE-2025-61729 — crypto/x509 (HIGH): DoS via crafted certificate.
CVE-2025-61729
# CVE-2026-25679 — net/url (HIGH): insufficient host/authority component validation in
# url.Parse (accepts certain invalid URLs that should be rejected). gosu parses no URLs.
CVE-2026-25679
# CVE-2026-32280 — crypto/x509 (HIGH): DoS in certificate-chain building.
CVE-2026-32280
# CVE-2026-32281 — crypto/x509 (HIGH): DoS via inefficient chain validation.
CVE-2026-32281
# CVE-2026-32283 — crypto/tls (HIGH): DoS via multiple TLS 1.3 key updates.
CVE-2026-32283
# CVE-2026-33811 — net (HIGH): cgo DNS LookupCNAME on long CNAME triggers double-free
# of C memory + crash (higher severity than DoS-only). gosu opens no sockets, runs no
# DNS lookups.
CVE-2026-33811
# CVE-2026-33814 — net/http2 (HIGH): infinite loop on crafted SETTINGS frames.
CVE-2026-33814
# CVE-2026-39820 — net/mail (HIGH): crafted input to ParseAddress / ParseAddressList.
CVE-2026-39820
# CVE-2026-39836 — net (HIGH): panic in Dial/LookupPort on NUL byte (Windows).
CVE-2026-39836
# CVE-2026-42499 — net/mail (HIGH): DoS via consumePhrase on pathological input.
CVE-2026-42499

# ─── Second wave (disclosed 2026-05-21 → 2026-05-26, same gosu binary) ───
# Same reachability story: gosu opens no sockets, parses no URLs / mail /
# archives / certificates, and does no TLS — so every one of these sits in
# unreachable code. Fixable only by an upstream gosu rebuild on a patched Go
# toolchain (Go 1.24.8+ / 1.25.2+ cover most; -61727 needs Go 1.24.11 / 1.25.5).
# Triggered the security-CI failure on PR #18.

# CVE-2025-47912 — net/url (HIGH): Parse permits non-IPv6 in bracketed-host form.
CVE-2025-47912
# CVE-2025-58185 — encoding/asn1 (HIGH): unbounded allocation parsing DER payload.
CVE-2025-58185
# CVE-2025-58186 — net/http (HIGH): default 1MB header limit can be bypassed.
CVE-2025-58186
# CVE-2025-58187 — crypto/x509 (HIGH): inefficient name-constraint check → DoS.
CVE-2025-58187
# CVE-2025-58188 — crypto/x509 (HIGH): DSA-public-key cert chain validation issue.
CVE-2025-58188
# CVE-2025-58189 — crypto/tls (HIGH): ALPN handshake error path information leak.
CVE-2025-58189
# CVE-2025-61723 — encoding/pem (HIGH): non-linear parse time on invalid PEM inputs;
# untrusted PEM data exhausts CPU. gosu parses no PEM data.
CVE-2025-61723
# CVE-2025-61724 — net/textproto (HIGH): Reader.ReadResponse response-building DoS.
CVE-2025-61724
# CVE-2025-61725 — net/mail (HIGH): ParseAddress domain-literal construction.
CVE-2025-61725
# CVE-2025-61727 — crypto/x509 (HIGH): excluded-subdomain constraint not enforced.
CVE-2025-61727

# ─── Third wave (disclosed 2026-05-26 → 2026-05-27, same gosu binary) ───
# Same reachability story as waves 1 + 2 reframed for these specific code paths:
# gosu is a setuid step-down wrapper that drops root and exec()s Postgres — it
# does not render HTML templates and does not run an HTTP server (let alone a
# reverse proxy). All three fixed in Go 1.25.10 / 1.26.3 (the same Go release
# that resolves five of the wave-2 entries); only an upstream gosu rebuild on
# a patched Go toolchain clears them.
#
# **Threshold tripped.** The WAIVERS.md pattern note (added 2026-05-26 after
# wave 2) recorded a "build our own image if this happens a third time" rule.
# Wave 3 trips it. Evaluation tracked in Issue #22 — this waiver extension is
# the *unblock* (so PR #21's CI can go green), not the resolution. Triggered
# the security-CI failure on PR #21.
#
# **Codex P2 correction (2026-05-27):** an earlier draft of these comments
# mis-attributed CVE-2026-39823 to `net/url` and justified it via "gosu parses
# no URLs". The actual CVE is in `html/template` (XSS via URLs inside a `<meta>`
# tag's content attribute), and the justification has to match the real code
# path. Rationale below now matches NVD + Go vuln-DB GO-2026-4982.

# CVE-2026-39823 — html/template (HIGH): URLs are not correctly escaped inside
# `<meta>` tag content attributes; ASCII whitespace around `=` bypasses the
# escaper, enabling XSS in rendered HTML. gosu renders no HTML templates, so
# the vulnerable code path is never executed.
CVE-2026-39823
# CVE-2026-39825 — net/http/httputil (HIGH): ReverseProxy forwards query
# parameters not visible to the configured Rewrite function once ParseQuery's
# parameter limit is exceeded. gosu runs no HTTP server, let alone a reverse
# proxy.
CVE-2026-39825
# CVE-2026-39826 — html/template (HIGH): incorrect data escaping when a
# `<script>` tag has an empty or whitespace-only `type` attribute, enabling
# XSS. gosu renders no HTML templates, so the vulnerable code path is never
# executed.
CVE-2026-39826
# CVE-2026-42504 — mime (HIGH): quadratic complexity in WordDecoder.DecodeHeader
# (CWE-407) — a crafted MIME header with many invalid encoded-words consumes
# excessive CPU (DoS). gosu decodes no MIME headers and takes no untrusted input,
# so the vulnerable path is never executed. (GO-2026-5038.)
CVE-2026-42504
